window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>After a burnt pot and subsequent call to the fire department, Martha’s buttoned-up lawyer son whisks her away from her Iowa home and installs her in an assisted living apartment at Martyn Manor in Poughkeepsie, New York.</p><p></p><p>Bored with her day-to-day routine, Martha finds ways to make her life, and the lives of her friends, more exciting. On top of late-night (by Manor standards) trips to the local college hangout, Martha morphs into an amateur sleuth who solves more than one crime. What really happened to sweet Harold Lancaster? What's the best way to catch a purse-snatcher? And what does that mysterious new resident have up her sleeve? </p><p></p><p>When Martha isn't looking for trouble, trouble is finding her - even on a transatlantic cruise!</p><p></p><p> <b><i>It’s (Mostly) Good To Be Martha</i></b> is a combination cozy mystery and romance with a heads-up on what the big Nine-O can look like if you’re willing to take chances, embrace the moment, and get into good-trouble</p>"; 
